WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:07.268
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:07.311 --> 00:08.921
<i>According to this map,
the one in Seattle</i>

00:08.965 --> 00:10.488
<i>is gonna open tomorrow.</i>

00:10.532 --> 00:12.577
That sinkhole
brought us to L.A.

00:12.621 --> 00:14.884
When I was a little girl,
I was kidnapped.

00:14.927 --> 00:16.320
<i>So was Veronica.</i>

00:16.364 --> 00:18.061
I wanted to get
down here to help.

00:18.105 --> 00:20.411
Isaiah is Gavin.

00:20.455 --> 00:21.934
I'm taking Isaiah to the light.

00:21.978 --> 00:23.240
<i>He has to get to 1988.</i>

00:23.284 --> 00:25.329
Take him up there,
the moment you go,

00:25.373 --> 00:26.809
I'll kill your son.

00:26.852 --> 00:28.071
[whirring]

00:28.115 --> 00:29.986
What is that?

00:30.030 --> 00:31.857
- Josh?
- Riley!

00:31.901 --> 00:32.989
Are we in 1988?

00:33.033 --> 00:34.425
Check this out.

00:35.252 --> 00:37.211
We may have found our
way back to 10,000 BC.

00:37.254 --> 00:39.343
I'm responsible for
these sinkholes opening.

00:39.387 --> 00:42.172
This is our way
into the building.

00:42.216 --> 00:43.260
Do you still love her?

00:43.304 --> 00:45.088
Gavin, I'm sorry.

00:45.132 --> 00:46.307
[gasps]

00:46.350 --> 00:47.438
Hey!
- [grunting]

00:47.482 --> 00:49.527
<i>I came back, gave myself up.</i>

00:49.571 --> 00:51.225
<i>I told you I wasn't
leaving you.</i>

00:53.096 --> 00:56.012
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:56.056 --> 01:03.150
<i>♪</i>

01:21.168 --> 01:22.734
Hello?

01:22.778 --> 01:24.127
I got the pliers.

01:24.171 --> 01:25.520
Hey.

01:25.563 --> 01:29.089
- What's up?
- Um, uh--it's just this--

01:29.132 --> 01:30.220
it's an inlet valve.

01:30.264 --> 01:33.136
I'm trying to replace it,
and it's shot.

01:33.180 --> 01:34.964
Where is everyone?

01:35.007 --> 01:36.313
Kids are at school.

01:36.357 --> 01:38.228
[sighs]
- And Gavin?

01:39.882 --> 01:42.058
[puts tool down]

01:42.102 --> 01:46.106
<i>♪</i>

01:46.149 --> 01:47.716
You know where Gavin is.

01:49.805 --> 01:52.677
He's come home drunk
every night this week.

01:52.721 --> 01:55.158
I just--I don't--

01:55.202 --> 01:57.117
I don't know what
to do anymore.

02:06.648 --> 02:08.998
I shouldn't--this is not--
this is not your problem.

02:09.041 --> 02:10.260
- Hey--
- I'm sorry.

02:10.304 --> 02:12.262
You don't have to
apologize for anything.

02:12.306 --> 02:13.829
You're doing
everything you can.

02:15.047 --> 02:16.614
[sniffling]

02:18.790 --> 02:19.835
Thank you.

02:21.402 --> 02:23.404
What are friends for?

02:23.447 --> 02:25.536
<i>[eerie music]</i>

02:25.580 --> 02:27.886
[rattling]

02:32.021 --> 02:34.676
<i>♪</i>

02:34.719 --> 02:35.764
[men shouting]

02:38.201 --> 02:39.855
Don't slow down. Come on!

02:40.725 --> 02:47.645
<i>♪</i>

02:53.869 --> 02:55.610
Move, now!

02:57.264 --> 02:58.656
Get 'em outta here.

02:58.700 --> 03:01.137
- Stop!
- Come on! Come on!

03:01.181 --> 03:02.486
Come on!

03:02.530 --> 03:05.359
[indistinct shouting]

03:09.798 --> 03:13.715
Keep moving!

03:13.758 --> 03:15.499
Move along!

03:15.543 --> 03:17.849
Shackles, come on!
Get 'em off, now!

03:17.893 --> 03:19.460
- What is this place?
- Come on!

03:19.503 --> 03:21.636
You! No talking!

03:21.679 --> 03:24.291
Hurry up!
Shackles off! You two--

03:24.334 --> 03:26.031
You two, tunnel nine.

03:26.075 --> 03:27.685
What do you want from us?

03:27.729 --> 03:29.600
[yelps]
- Son of a bitch!

03:29.644 --> 03:31.907
[grunting]

03:31.950 --> 03:33.735
- Levi!
- Enough!

03:34.910 --> 03:36.259
No time for this!

03:36.303 --> 03:38.218
<i>[intense music]</i>

03:38.261 --> 03:40.437
Get back to work.

03:40.481 --> 03:43.048
You heard Taamit. Move!

03:43.092 --> 03:45.312
<i>♪</i>

03:46.965 --> 03:50.317
<i>[eerie music]</i>

03:50.360 --> 03:52.275
Eve?

03:52.319 --> 03:53.755
Josh?

03:53.798 --> 03:58.890
<i>♪</i>

03:58.934 --> 04:00.588
Eve!

04:02.372 --> 04:04.113
Who are you?

04:04.156 --> 04:06.115
My name is Gavin Harris.

04:06.158 --> 04:07.769
This is Ella, my daughter Izzy.

04:10.206 --> 04:12.295
But you knew me as Isaiah.

04:12.339 --> 04:14.428
- Isaiah?
- Yeah.

04:16.256 --> 04:17.648
I remember you.

04:17.692 --> 04:19.868
You bandaged my hand
in that bus over there.

04:21.783 --> 04:22.827
My God.

04:25.439 --> 04:28.920
Everyone, it's Eve's husband!

04:28.964 --> 04:30.095
Josh's dad.

04:30.139 --> 04:33.447
It's Isaiah, Isaiah grown up.

04:33.490 --> 04:35.187
Hey, do you have some water?
For--

04:35.231 --> 04:36.798
Yeah.
Let's get some water.

04:37.886 --> 04:39.409
It's unbelievable.

04:40.976 --> 04:42.456
How did you get here?

04:42.499 --> 04:44.327
We went through
a sinkhole in Seattle

04:44.371 --> 04:45.894
that somehow brought us
here to L.A.

04:45.937 --> 04:48.113
Wait,
you're here to rescue us?

04:48.157 --> 04:50.986
Look, I'm sorry. We--

04:51.029 --> 04:52.379
We don't have any way home.

04:53.554 --> 04:55.425
Listen, I'm here to
find my family, my--

04:55.469 --> 04:57.558
my son, my wife.

05:02.389 --> 05:04.434
Are they OK?

05:04.478 --> 05:06.436
We don't know.

05:06.480 --> 05:08.133
Where the hell are they?

05:08.177 --> 05:10.614
Eve was captured.

05:10.658 --> 05:12.660
Some people took her and Levi.

05:14.009 --> 05:15.097
What about Josh?

05:15.140 --> 05:16.490
When you went
through the portal,

05:16.533 --> 05:17.621
it expanded.

05:17.665 --> 05:19.449
Josh and my daughter Riley,

05:19.493 --> 05:21.103
they went through to 1988.

05:21.146 --> 05:22.234
What?

05:22.278 --> 05:23.801
Yeah, and a young girl,

05:23.845 --> 05:25.803
Lilly, she went through,
as well.

05:25.847 --> 05:28.850
I didn't remember
them going through.

05:28.893 --> 05:30.155
I don't follow.

05:30.199 --> 05:32.332
Why would you remember?

05:32.375 --> 05:36.466
Because, Ty, I'm Lilly.

05:36.510 --> 05:38.686
But now my name is Ella.

05:40.383 --> 05:42.080
Is it really you?

05:42.907 --> 05:45.867
<i>[tender music]</i>

05:45.910 --> 05:48.652
<i>♪</i>

05:48.696 --> 05:50.698
OK, this is
officially insane.

05:52.874 --> 05:56.007
Dad, we came all this way,
and now they're just gone.

05:56.051 --> 05:59.707
No, no.
We're gonna get them back, OK?

06:00.447 --> 06:02.144
OK.

06:02.187 --> 06:05.321
Hey, you said that Eve and
Levi were taken by some people.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.236
Who were they?
- I'm not sure, man.

06:07.279 --> 06:08.455
I mean, they were armed.

06:08.498 --> 06:10.195
They had machetes,
rode horseback.

06:10.239 --> 06:11.545
Did they have wagons?

06:11.588 --> 06:13.373
Yeah, they did.
How'd you know that?

06:13.416 --> 06:14.809
It's 'cause
he was a boy here.

06:14.852 --> 06:16.680
I remember stories about
a violent group of people

06:16.724 --> 06:18.639
that used wagons and
horses to enslave

06:18.682 --> 06:21.685
anyone who came on their land.

06:21.729 --> 06:24.384
They were called the Exiles.

06:24.427 --> 06:25.733
My grandfather
warned me about them,

06:25.776 --> 06:27.212
but he never told
me where they lived.

06:27.256 --> 06:29.824
[crowd chattering]

06:29.867 --> 06:31.086
What?

06:32.479 --> 06:33.871
What is it?

06:33.915 --> 06:36.047
Your grandfather,
he's here with us.

06:38.615 --> 06:41.052
- Where is he?
- We're holding him.

06:41.096 --> 06:42.445
We're trying to get
him to help us find

06:42.489 --> 06:44.142
this woman named Aldridge.

06:44.186 --> 06:45.405
You've seen Aldridge?

06:45.448 --> 06:47.145
Yes, but she's been
missing for days.

06:47.189 --> 06:49.496
We think she can help us
get Josh and Riley back.

06:49.539 --> 06:51.149
Silas knows where she is.

06:51.193 --> 06:52.412
He gave us a lead.

06:52.455 --> 06:53.674
Eve and Levi went
out to check it out,

06:53.717 --> 06:54.979
but they never came back.

06:55.023 --> 06:57.982
Well, I know he can
help me find the Exiles.

06:58.026 --> 07:00.637
Take me to him.

07:00.681 --> 07:02.422
- This way.
- OK.

07:04.119 --> 07:07.644
Be careful. Hey, he may have
raised you, but he's dangerous.

07:07.688 --> 07:09.472
He kidnapped Eve and Levi.

07:09.516 --> 07:11.126
He was ready to
kill your children.

07:11.169 --> 07:13.128
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:13.171 --> 07:14.477
I remember.

07:14.521 --> 07:18.525
<i>♪</i>

07:20.701 --> 07:22.093
[tarp rustling]

07:23.704 --> 07:26.663
<i>[ominous music]</i>

07:26.707 --> 07:33.148
<i>♪</i>

07:34.410 --> 07:36.064
Hello, my boy.

07:39.110 --> 07:40.764
You remember me.

07:41.722 --> 07:43.201
Welcome home.

07:43.245 --> 07:46.204
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:46.248 --> 07:51.079
<i>♪</i>

07:56.780 --> 08:00.088
[indistinct chatter]

08:08.923 --> 08:10.054
If we can get
to that sinkhole,

08:10.098 --> 08:12.622
it will take us
back to 10,000 BC.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.232
So, how do we do this?

08:14.276 --> 08:15.756
We act cool.

08:15.799 --> 08:18.672
And when these cops move,
we slip under the barrier,

08:18.715 --> 08:20.587
run up to the hole, and jump.

08:21.501 --> 08:22.719
That's your idea?

08:22.763 --> 08:24.504
We just run up there
in broad daylight?

08:24.547 --> 08:25.940
We have to.

08:25.983 --> 08:27.507
This is the only way to
get back to our families.

08:27.550 --> 08:29.334
And besides, we don't know
when that thing's gonna close.

08:29.378 --> 08:31.075
No, there has to
be a better plan.

08:31.119 --> 08:32.599
There's too many cops.

08:32.642 --> 08:34.644
Who we can outrun.

08:34.688 --> 08:36.254
OK, so we get caught.

08:36.298 --> 08:37.865
What do we say?

08:37.908 --> 08:39.431
That there's way more
going on with these sinkholes

08:39.475 --> 08:40.476
than anyone knows.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.347
Do you hear yourself?

08:42.391 --> 08:43.871
They'll think we're insane.

08:43.914 --> 08:46.743
That's why
we can't get caught.

08:46.787 --> 08:49.050
Look, Josh, we both
want to see our families.

08:49.093 --> 08:51.705
But we have to be
smart about this.

08:51.748 --> 08:53.445
We'll come back at night.

08:53.489 --> 08:56.274
It's dark, less cops.

08:56.318 --> 08:58.146
Agreed?

08:58.189 --> 08:59.451
Yeah.

08:59.495 --> 09:03.281
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:03.325 --> 09:05.632
Keep moving!

09:05.675 --> 09:08.635
You have one job
and one job only.

09:08.678 --> 09:11.246
Find this rock.

09:11.289 --> 09:14.336
When you find some,
tell the guard immediately.

09:14.379 --> 09:15.555
Then keep digging.

09:15.598 --> 09:17.818
You get it! Dig!

09:18.775 --> 09:20.603
Dig! I said, move!

09:20.647 --> 09:22.562
[men shouting]
Come on, faster.

09:27.523 --> 09:29.220
Guards! I got one.

09:36.750 --> 09:39.013
What do you think
that black rock is?

09:39.056 --> 09:40.536
I don't know.

09:41.537 --> 09:43.104
Maybe he does.

09:49.937 --> 09:51.678
Hey.

09:51.721 --> 09:53.810
We just got here.

09:53.854 --> 09:57.335
You been in this place long?
- Not too long--

09:57.379 --> 09:59.294
I think.
It's hard to keep track.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.691
I'm Virgil.

10:04.734 --> 10:07.128
Virgil,
where did you come from?

10:07.171 --> 10:09.173
Los Angeles.

10:09.217 --> 10:12.089
Fell through a sinkhole up by
the Tar Pits,

10:12.133 --> 10:13.525
same as them.

10:13.569 --> 10:15.919
About a dozen of us here.
- Us, too.

10:15.963 --> 10:18.879
We've been living in a clearing
about 10 miles west of here.

10:18.922 --> 10:21.142
What do you know about these
people who are holding us?

10:21.185 --> 10:23.361
They're brutal.

10:23.405 --> 10:25.755
Make us dig.

10:25.799 --> 10:28.062
Take what we find
and put it in these crates.

10:28.105 --> 10:29.193
To go where?

10:29.237 --> 10:30.673
No one knows, man.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.153
On your feet!

10:32.196 --> 10:33.589
Want my advice?

10:33.633 --> 10:37.462
Keep your head down,
and do exactly what they say.

10:37.506 --> 10:39.943
You step out of line,
these people will kill you.

10:39.987 --> 10:41.379
Hey!

10:41.423 --> 10:42.685
Keep digging.

10:42.729 --> 10:46.080
[rocks clattering]

10:49.649 --> 10:51.389
I need your help.

10:51.433 --> 10:54.392
Some people have taken
my wife and my friend.

10:54.436 --> 10:56.264
I think it was the Exiles.

10:56.307 --> 10:57.787
Can you help me find them?

10:58.570 --> 11:00.703
You're my grandson.

11:00.747 --> 11:02.139
I'll do anything you ask.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.012
Thank you.

11:05.055 --> 11:07.318
Where the Exiles live
is difficult

11:07.362 --> 11:10.887
to access, dangerous.

11:10.931 --> 11:12.454
But I can show you the way.

11:12.497 --> 11:16.284
No, these people aren't
gonna let you just leave.

11:20.375 --> 11:22.638
You're just gonna have to
tell me how to get there.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.248
That's not possible.

11:24.292 --> 11:26.468
I have to go with you,
and it can only be us.

11:26.511 --> 11:27.643
- No--
- No, we can't risk

11:27.687 --> 11:29.558
being exposed.
- Stop. Stop!

11:29.601 --> 11:30.777
I know what you're doing.

11:30.820 --> 11:32.822
- I'm offering to help.
- No.

11:32.866 --> 11:35.259
You're trying to use me
so that you can escape.

11:35.303 --> 11:36.521
That's all.

11:36.565 --> 11:40.612
The Exiles are merciless.

11:40.656 --> 11:43.093
You remember the stories,
don't you?

11:43.137 --> 11:46.836
They'll kill your
wife and your friend

11:46.880 --> 11:49.230
and never think twice about it.

11:49.273 --> 11:51.623
You want to see
them alive again,

11:51.667 --> 11:53.756
then we need to leave now.

11:53.800 --> 11:56.803
And you need to listen to me.

12:01.198 --> 12:03.157
- Where to?
- This way.

12:03.200 --> 12:05.202
Whoa, whoa.
What's going on?

12:05.246 --> 12:07.248
Silas is bringing
me to the Exiles.

12:07.291 --> 12:08.945
Gavin, wait.

12:08.989 --> 12:10.294
Look, we promised Paara
we'd take Silas

12:10.338 --> 12:11.556
back to her village.

12:11.600 --> 12:12.949
Our relationship with
them depends on it.

12:12.993 --> 12:14.385
We can't go back on our word.
- I'm sorry,

12:14.429 --> 12:15.778
but Eve's life is on the line.

12:15.822 --> 12:18.302
- We're going with you.
- No no, no. You can't.

12:18.346 --> 12:20.391
Silas has intel on how
to get my daughter back.

12:20.435 --> 12:22.132
I need to make sure he
doesn't try and escape.

12:22.176 --> 12:24.178
Dad, listen to them.
You can't go alone.

12:24.221 --> 12:25.788
Iz, it has to be just me
and him.

12:25.832 --> 12:26.920
It's the only way
he's gonna help me.

12:26.963 --> 12:28.660
You cannot trust him, Gavin.

12:28.704 --> 12:30.401
Remember what he's done.

12:30.445 --> 12:31.968
- I can't let you do this.
- Hey, hey,

12:32.012 --> 12:33.317
we're gonna
save Josh and Riley.

12:33.361 --> 12:34.754
But right now,
these people have Eve,

12:34.797 --> 12:36.146
and I have to take Silas.

12:38.366 --> 12:39.846
Please.

12:47.070 --> 12:48.985
Promise me you won't
let him out of your sight,

12:49.029 --> 12:50.334
and you'll get him back here.

12:55.296 --> 12:57.515
Yeah.

12:57.559 --> 12:58.908
Wait, Dad, Dad.

12:58.952 --> 13:01.868
Iz, I need you to
stay with them, OK?

13:05.828 --> 13:08.135
Be careful.

13:08.178 --> 13:10.006
I'll be back
as fast as I can.

13:10.050 --> 13:12.400
When I am, I'll have
Mom and Levi with me.

13:16.317 --> 13:17.971
Come on.

13:18.014 --> 13:20.930
<i>[tense music]</i>

13:20.974 --> 13:28.111
<i>♪</i>

13:32.855 --> 13:35.162
<i>[INXS's "New Sensation"]</i>

13:35.205 --> 13:38.034
<i>♪ Live, baby, live</i>

13:38.078 --> 13:40.123
<i>♪ Now that the day is over</i>

13:40.167 --> 13:41.603
Thank you.

13:41.646 --> 13:42.822
Mmm.

13:42.865 --> 13:44.954
These really are
the best since 1988.

13:44.998 --> 13:46.521
What are you talking about?

13:46.564 --> 13:48.740
This is my dad's
favorite spot.

13:48.784 --> 13:49.916
He grew up here.

13:49.959 --> 13:51.439
He used to bring me
here all the time.

13:51.482 --> 13:52.962
They have this giant
sign that says,

13:53.006 --> 13:55.182
"LA's best dogs since 1988."

13:57.488 --> 14:00.622
Or they will.
[people screaming on ride]

14:00.665 --> 14:01.884
I've never thought
about this before,

14:01.928 --> 14:03.755
but I could totally
run into my dad here.

14:03.799 --> 14:05.583
How crazy would that be?

14:05.627 --> 14:07.542
Would it be as crazy
as hanging out with

14:07.585 --> 14:09.109
your 10-year-old father,
and then

14:09.152 --> 14:11.851
sending him through a light
in the sky so you don't die?

14:11.894 --> 14:14.331
Good point.
[laughs]

14:17.465 --> 14:19.684
Josh. Josh, look at that
guy over there.

14:21.338 --> 14:22.818
I think I saw him
at the sinkhole.

14:22.862 --> 14:23.993
Yeah, so?

14:24.037 --> 14:25.821
So do you think
he's following us?

14:25.865 --> 14:26.866
Why would he do that?

14:26.909 --> 14:28.215
It's probably just
a coincidence.

14:29.477 --> 14:31.174
You're being a little paranoid.

14:31.218 --> 14:33.916
OK, well, there's only
one way to find out.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.787
What are you doing?

14:35.831 --> 14:37.746
Sorry to bother you.

14:37.789 --> 14:38.921
Are you stalking us?

14:38.965 --> 14:41.445
Me?

14:41.489 --> 14:42.664
No.

14:44.100 --> 14:45.623
You sure about that?

14:49.018 --> 14:51.281
OK, I am following you.

14:51.325 --> 14:53.109
Not stalking.
There's a difference.

14:53.153 --> 14:54.850
- I knew it.
- I overheard you talking

14:54.894 --> 14:56.808
at the Hollywood sign.

14:56.852 --> 14:59.115
You said, there's way more
going on with these sinkholes

14:59.159 --> 15:01.117
than anyone knows.

15:01.161 --> 15:03.206
Thing is, you're right.

15:04.512 --> 15:06.340
You're not the only
one to think that.

15:07.341 --> 15:08.646
I do, too.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.172
Who the hell are you?

15:12.215 --> 15:13.651
I'm--I'm Franklin Marsh.

15:13.695 --> 15:15.871
I'm a professor of
geology at Cal Tech.

15:17.568 --> 15:19.005
We have a lot to discuss.

15:19.048 --> 15:22.008
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:22.051 --> 15:25.272
<i>♪</i>

15:29.754 --> 15:31.452
[chuckles]

15:31.495 --> 15:33.671
You recognize this place?

15:33.715 --> 15:36.848
These woods are where I
first taught you to hunt.

15:36.892 --> 15:40.156
That's where you killed
your first wild pig.

15:40.200 --> 15:41.810
It was a mean one, too.

15:43.812 --> 15:46.206
You needed my help,
if you remember.

15:52.038 --> 15:54.823
Please, Gavin.

15:54.866 --> 15:56.738
No, I'm not
cutting you loose.

15:56.781 --> 15:58.435
You bring me to Eve,
I'll consider it.

15:58.479 --> 15:59.871
There was a time
you used to trust me.

15:59.915 --> 16:01.351
Yeah, there was.

16:01.395 --> 16:03.571
And then you hurt my wife,

16:03.614 --> 16:05.703
threatened my children.

16:07.879 --> 16:10.752
What if I told you I did
those things to protect you?

16:10.795 --> 16:12.319
<i>[dark tone]</i>

16:12.362 --> 16:15.235
I raised you,

16:15.278 --> 16:16.758
loved you unconditionally.

16:16.801 --> 16:18.586
I still do.

16:18.629 --> 16:20.718
You know, if that were true,

16:20.762 --> 16:23.199
you would have told Eve how to
bring Josh back right away.

16:23.243 --> 16:24.331
It's not that simple.

16:24.374 --> 16:26.942
No?

16:26.986 --> 16:28.248
Why not?

16:30.076 --> 16:31.425
Why not?

16:32.774 --> 16:34.819
Is there a way to
bring my son back?

16:38.432 --> 16:39.911
I don't know.

16:41.522 --> 16:43.002
You're lying to me.

16:44.351 --> 16:46.831
You wanna know why
I don't trust you?

16:49.530 --> 16:50.879
There's your answer.

17:03.152 --> 17:04.632
Veronica?

17:07.156 --> 17:09.028
Do I know you?

17:10.681 --> 17:14.381
I know you don't
recognize me, but...

17:14.424 --> 17:17.993
it's me, Lilly.

17:18.037 --> 17:21.344
I went through the light,
but now I'm back.

17:22.867 --> 17:25.827
<i>[tender music]</i>

17:25.870 --> 17:31.833
<i>♪</i>

17:31.876 --> 17:34.401
Oh, my God.

17:34.444 --> 17:37.491
[laughs] Lilly.

17:37.534 --> 17:44.063
<i>♪</i>

17:57.815 --> 18:00.166
[creaking]
[footsteps approaching]

18:00.209 --> 18:03.125
Your mom and
Josh slept there.

18:03.169 --> 18:05.562
Yeah, I figured.

18:05.606 --> 18:07.042
You know,
if you're interested,

18:07.086 --> 18:08.696
we've got some stuff to do.

18:08.739 --> 18:12.830
Search party's gone out to
find a friend of ours, Scott.

18:12.874 --> 18:14.267
A few others are
clearing the fields

18:14.310 --> 18:15.485
so we can start planting crops.

18:15.529 --> 18:17.531
You can help.
- I'm fine here.

18:17.574 --> 18:19.837
Thanks, though.
- I saw you limping earlier.

18:19.881 --> 18:21.274
You in pain?

18:21.317 --> 18:22.318
Not really.

18:22.362 --> 18:25.974
[chuckles] You're tough.

18:26.017 --> 18:28.150
Just like your mom.

18:28.194 --> 18:30.892
Let me guess, limb abrasion.

18:32.198 --> 18:33.590
My socket got cracked.

18:33.634 --> 18:36.593
Oh, that was my second guess.

18:36.637 --> 18:39.596
So I came prepared.

18:39.640 --> 18:43.600
Got some tape, little tar
from the tar pit over there.

18:43.644 --> 18:45.776
I know it sounds low tech,

18:45.820 --> 18:48.562
but I think it'll do the trick.

18:50.564 --> 18:52.131
How do you know all this?

18:52.174 --> 18:55.177
I worked with the
Wounded Warriors program.

18:55.221 --> 18:57.658
I spent a lot of time
with vets and prosthetics.

18:57.701 --> 18:59.442
Can I take a look?

19:03.968 --> 19:06.057
Yep, there it is.

19:06.101 --> 19:07.102
OK.

19:10.932 --> 19:13.152
Why do I feel like
I've met you before?

19:13.195 --> 19:16.938
[chuckles] My son says I've
got one of those faces.

19:20.420 --> 19:22.857
Your last name
isn't Velez, is it?

19:24.424 --> 19:26.687
How'd you know?

19:26.730 --> 19:29.168
I go to school
with your son Andrew.

19:29.211 --> 19:30.778
I was at a vigil with him.

19:30.821 --> 19:32.649
He showed me a picture
of you and his sister.

19:32.693 --> 19:34.173
You were with Andrew?

19:37.350 --> 19:39.439
Is he OK?

19:39.482 --> 19:42.224
He misses you a lot,

19:42.268 --> 19:43.965
but he hasn't lost hope.

19:47.882 --> 19:50.189
Uh--

19:50.232 --> 19:54.236
Sorry your brother
wasn't here to meet you.

19:54.976 --> 19:58.414
Everything with him and
Riley happened so fast.

19:58.458 --> 20:00.155
They're gonna be OK.

20:01.548 --> 20:03.593
My brother has
always protected me,

20:03.637 --> 20:05.552
so I know he'll watch
out for your daughter.

20:08.642 --> 20:10.687
We're gonna get them both back.

20:10.731 --> 20:12.211
I know we will.

20:16.084 --> 20:17.259
Thirsty?

20:17.303 --> 20:18.478
Thanks.

20:25.311 --> 20:27.443
I still can't believe it.

20:27.487 --> 20:31.708
I know, but it's me.

20:36.626 --> 20:41.849
So, how much you remember
about me?

20:41.892 --> 20:44.634
About us?

20:44.678 --> 20:47.637
You mean,
you, me, and Aaron?

20:51.380 --> 20:53.034
I remember everything.

20:54.818 --> 20:57.734
<i>[somber music]</i>

20:57.778 --> 21:00.433
<i>♪</i>

21:00.476 --> 21:02.826
I'm sorry.

21:02.870 --> 21:05.220
It's my fault you never got
the childhood you deserve.

21:05.264 --> 21:07.266
I don't blame you.

21:07.309 --> 21:10.051
If it weren't for you,

21:10.094 --> 21:12.836
I wouldn't have made it
through any of what happened.

21:16.884 --> 21:20.322
I owe you, Veronica.

21:20.366 --> 21:21.584
That's why I came back.

21:21.628 --> 21:24.283
What do you mean?

21:24.326 --> 21:26.502
I knew you were in trouble.

21:26.546 --> 21:28.287
You needed help, so I came.

21:29.897 --> 21:31.942
You came back just for me?

21:31.986 --> 21:33.074
Yes.

21:33.117 --> 21:34.771
You would have done
the same for me.

21:37.818 --> 21:39.298
You shouldn't have done that.

21:39.341 --> 21:41.387
Veronica, wait.

21:41.430 --> 21:48.568
<i>♪</i>

21:52.963 --> 21:55.879
I realize you're
upset with me.

21:55.923 --> 21:57.751
But I know this land
better than you.

21:57.794 --> 22:00.319
You need to listen.
- No.

22:00.362 --> 22:02.059
I'm not a little boy anymore.

22:02.103 --> 22:03.713
You have so
much anger inside.

22:03.757 --> 22:05.672
Yeah, because you lied to me.

22:05.715 --> 22:07.369
- I never lied.
- Really?

22:07.413 --> 22:09.980
Hey, so tell me, then,

22:10.024 --> 22:11.460
why do we live in that village?

22:11.504 --> 22:12.592
Where do we come from?

22:12.635 --> 22:14.811
What happened to my parents?

22:14.855 --> 22:16.857
- They died.
- They died how?

22:16.900 --> 22:18.598
[rustling]
- Shh.

22:20.077 --> 22:21.165
There's something out there.

22:21.209 --> 22:22.776
[sighs]

22:25.213 --> 22:27.041
[grunts]

22:31.785 --> 22:33.917
All right.
[unsheathes knife]

22:33.961 --> 22:35.745
[grunts]

22:35.789 --> 22:37.660
Silas, hey, hey.

22:37.704 --> 22:39.662
Pass me the knife.

22:39.706 --> 22:42.186
Silas? Yeah.

22:42.230 --> 22:43.274
Hey, cut me down.

22:43.318 --> 22:44.363
Hey.

22:44.406 --> 22:46.408
Silas!
Cut me down!

22:46.452 --> 22:47.888
Silas! Hey!

22:51.500 --> 22:52.588
Silas, come back!

22:52.632 --> 22:54.895
[grunting]

22:54.938 --> 22:57.985
[snarling, growling]

23:01.597 --> 23:04.905
[huffing, growling]

23:07.951 --> 23:12.042
Easy, easy, easy.

23:12.086 --> 23:15.394
[roars]
Easy, easy, shh. OK, OK.

23:18.484 --> 23:19.920
[roars]

23:19.963 --> 23:22.183
Easy.
[shushing]

23:24.620 --> 23:27.841
[roaring]
Hey! Hey!

23:27.884 --> 23:29.103
Please! Hey, no!

23:29.146 --> 23:31.453
No, no, no!
[bear whimpers, groans]

23:31.497 --> 23:32.976
[thud]

23:35.675 --> 23:38.199
Silas.
[panting]

23:39.853 --> 23:41.507
[grunts]

23:51.952 --> 23:53.997
[grunts]

23:57.610 --> 23:59.481
Uh!

23:59.525 --> 24:02.005
[panting]

24:05.661 --> 24:08.795
Thought you left.

24:08.838 --> 24:11.798
I would never
leave you, my boy.

24:11.841 --> 24:13.800
Thank you.

24:13.843 --> 24:15.541
Come on.

24:15.584 --> 24:19.370
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:20.981 --> 24:22.461
Pick that up!

24:22.504 --> 24:24.158
You! No talking!

24:24.201 --> 24:25.812
Take that outside!
[metal clanking]

24:25.855 --> 24:27.596
Hey! Come on! Faster!

24:29.555 --> 24:31.513
[tool clattering]

24:31.557 --> 24:33.254
<i>I've gotta go.</i>

24:33.907 --> 24:37.127
- Or you can stay.
- Mm, I wish.

24:39.565 --> 24:43.003
I gotta go make dinner
before the kids come home.

24:43.046 --> 24:44.439
Mm-mm, mm-mm.

24:44.483 --> 24:46.093
[chuckles]

24:51.664 --> 24:53.404
[sighs]

24:59.759 --> 25:01.325
What are we doing here, Eve?

25:01.369 --> 25:03.284
I think it's pretty
obvious what we're doing.

25:04.894 --> 25:06.330
How much longer
are we gonna keep

25:06.374 --> 25:07.984
sneaking around like this?

25:08.028 --> 25:10.160
I don't know what
you want me to say.

25:14.513 --> 25:16.515
I think you
deserve to be happy.

25:21.215 --> 25:24.174
To be in a solid relationship,
out in the open.

25:24.218 --> 25:25.959
It would be good for
you and the kids.

25:26.002 --> 25:27.700
I gotta go.

25:27.743 --> 25:30.703
<i>[tender music]</i>

25:30.746 --> 25:36.926
<i>♪</i>

25:36.970 --> 25:39.102
Eve...

25:41.278 --> 25:43.063
I'd really
like to talk about this.

25:43.106 --> 25:44.630
It's just not that simple.

25:47.023 --> 25:48.459
Then explain it to me.

25:53.943 --> 25:56.293
My dad had an affair.

25:56.337 --> 25:58.557
He left my mom,
and I never got over it.

26:00.341 --> 26:01.734
I didn't speak
to him for years.

26:01.777 --> 26:03.126
I'm sorry.

26:03.170 --> 26:05.781
I was 15, Levi.

26:05.825 --> 26:07.435
I was Izzy's age.

26:07.478 --> 26:11.744
<i>♪</i>

26:11.787 --> 26:14.137
[phone buzzing]

26:16.792 --> 26:18.098
Hello?

26:20.187 --> 26:22.058
Wait a minute. What--
I can't hear you. What?

26:22.102 --> 26:23.538
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait--
Is she OK?

26:25.279 --> 26:28.587
Yeah. No, I'll be right there.
I'll be right there.

26:28.630 --> 26:30.153
- What happened?
- Izzy was in an accident.

26:30.197 --> 26:31.633
- Is she all right?
- I don't know.

26:31.677 --> 26:33.635
My neighbor was driving,
and I--I was supposed to

26:33.679 --> 26:34.941
pick her up from school,
and I wasn't there.

26:34.984 --> 26:35.898
I have to go.
- Eve, it's--

26:35.942 --> 26:37.770
I gotta go!

26:37.813 --> 26:39.510
[men shouting]

26:44.385 --> 26:46.343
- What is it?
- I can't die in here, Levi.

26:47.562 --> 26:48.737
Not without seeing
my kids again.

26:50.913 --> 26:53.089
We have to find a way out.

26:53.133 --> 26:56.092
<i>[ominous music]</i>

26:56.136 --> 26:58.442
<i>♪</i>

26:58.486 --> 27:00.096
Move!

27:10.193 --> 27:11.760
Can we talk?

27:20.856 --> 27:24.338
Besides the cave, are
there any other entrances?

27:24.381 --> 27:26.688
That gate's the only way in.

27:26.732 --> 27:29.038
Heard rumors there
might be another way out

27:29.082 --> 27:30.561
through the tunnels.

27:31.998 --> 27:33.390
Not without a map.

27:36.002 --> 27:39.919
If we take out the guards,
sneak out through the gate,

27:39.962 --> 27:41.660
we just need a distraction.

27:41.703 --> 27:43.705
Can you help us?

27:43.749 --> 27:45.011
Me?

27:45.054 --> 27:46.360
Hey, listen.

27:46.403 --> 27:48.231
There are more of us
than there are of them.

27:48.275 --> 27:50.364
Back home, I was a chef,
all right?

27:50.407 --> 27:51.800
I've never been in
a fight in my life.

27:51.844 --> 27:53.759
You told us there was
a dozen other prisoners

27:53.802 --> 27:55.978
here from La Brea.

27:56.022 --> 27:58.111
If we get them on board,

27:58.154 --> 28:00.287
I think we can overpower
the guards.

28:04.900 --> 28:06.728
[sighs]

28:06.772 --> 28:09.644
All right,
I'll see what I can do.

28:09.688 --> 28:12.603
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

28:12.647 --> 28:16.085
<i>♪</i>

28:21.395 --> 28:23.832
Three years ago,
a sinkhole opened up

28:23.876 --> 28:26.356
in the Angeles Forest
unlike anything I'd ever seen.

28:26.400 --> 28:28.619
I went years after, searching
for another like it.

28:28.663 --> 28:32.754
Then, a week ago, one opens up
in the Topanga Canyon.

28:32.798 --> 28:35.235
Let me guess, same thing
at the Hollywood sign.

28:35.278 --> 28:37.628
Every time one of them opens,
their energy waves

28:37.672 --> 28:40.588
coincide with the time factor
that consistently

28:40.631 --> 28:41.720
predict the next one.

28:41.763 --> 28:43.722
Dude, English, please.

28:43.765 --> 28:45.941
More sinkholes are coming.

28:45.985 --> 28:47.638
Like, soon?

28:47.682 --> 28:50.163
Try four days.

28:50.206 --> 28:51.686
And it's gonna be really bad.

28:53.383 --> 28:55.429
Have you told anyone
else about this?

28:55.472 --> 28:58.737
Everyone I can,
but no one believes me.

28:58.780 --> 29:01.174
Look, this is all
super interesting.

29:01.217 --> 29:03.350
But why are you
telling this to us?

29:03.393 --> 29:05.352
When I heard you talking,
I figured

29:05.395 --> 29:07.136
you might have information
that could help

29:07.180 --> 29:09.138
prove what I'm saying is true.

29:09.182 --> 29:11.401
You need to tell
me what you know.

29:11.445 --> 29:14.970
Everyone in this area,
they're all in danger.

29:15.014 --> 29:16.580
What are you talking about?

29:16.624 --> 29:18.800
The next sinkhole
that's coming,

29:18.844 --> 29:22.021
it has the potential to destroy
a huge part of the city.

29:23.762 --> 29:27.504
I have to figure out how to
prove what I'm saying is true,

29:27.548 --> 29:29.550
and I need your help to do it.

29:29.593 --> 29:32.553
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:32.596 --> 29:35.077
The Exiles are just
beyond that next rise.

29:35.121 --> 29:36.949
And then what?

29:36.992 --> 29:38.341
There's a back
entrance we can

29:38.385 --> 29:40.691
slip into without being seen.

29:40.735 --> 29:43.694
When it comes near dark,
we'll make our move.

29:43.738 --> 29:45.348
For now,

29:45.392 --> 29:49.178
tell me about your life,
Gavin--

29:49.222 --> 29:51.528
who you became,
what you've done.

29:52.442 --> 29:56.664
Um, well, after I
went through the light,

29:56.707 --> 30:00.363
I got taken in by
some good people.

30:00.407 --> 30:01.669
They became my family.

30:03.453 --> 30:06.892
I guess I grew up like
most kids up there.

30:06.935 --> 30:10.547
And I went to college, joined
the Air Force,

30:10.591 --> 30:11.679
I became a pilot.

30:13.942 --> 30:16.858
Then I met Eve.

30:16.902 --> 30:19.382
We had Izzy and Josh.

30:19.426 --> 30:22.690
Then, uh--well,
then I let them down.

30:25.475 --> 30:27.260
Is it too late to
set things right?

30:29.088 --> 30:33.309
Honestly, I don't know.

30:34.528 --> 30:39.838
That's why I'm down here,
to find out.

30:39.881 --> 30:42.797
I understand regret.

30:42.841 --> 30:44.886
Believe me, I have my own.

30:44.930 --> 30:47.541
Like our family?

30:47.584 --> 30:49.282
My parents?

30:53.199 --> 30:55.331
Hey, look, you gotta
tell me something.

30:57.333 --> 30:58.944
My whole life,
I never knew who I really was

30:58.987 --> 31:01.424
where I came from.

31:01.468 --> 31:03.905
Can you imagine
what that's like?

31:03.949 --> 31:06.212
Can you?

31:06.255 --> 31:08.431
You gotta at least
tell me how they died.

31:11.608 --> 31:13.349
Your mother was
the single most

31:13.393 --> 31:16.875
important person in my life.

31:16.918 --> 31:20.226
She told me to care
for you, protect you,

31:20.269 --> 31:24.621
tell you only what you
needed to know to survive

31:24.665 --> 31:27.537
until she could see you again.

31:27.581 --> 31:29.191
You're saying she's alive?

31:30.758 --> 31:32.891
Your father, too.

31:32.934 --> 31:35.284
Whoa, hey--

31:35.328 --> 31:38.461
If my parents are alive,
and they're down here--

31:38.505 --> 31:39.593
are they down here?

31:39.636 --> 31:41.247
Gavin, please understand.

31:41.290 --> 31:42.639
You can't go looking for them.

31:42.683 --> 31:43.640
Why not?

31:43.684 --> 31:45.729
Because it may
mean your life.

31:45.773 --> 31:48.167
That's why I told you they
were dead, to protect you.

31:48.210 --> 31:49.646
Protect me from what?

31:49.690 --> 31:51.170
If my parents are down here,
I deserve the truth.

31:51.213 --> 31:52.780
You do.

31:52.823 --> 31:56.479
But I made a promise,
and I intend to keep it.

31:56.523 --> 31:59.395
There's a spring over there.

32:00.919 --> 32:02.355
I'm gonna fill my canteen.

32:05.836 --> 32:07.490
Let's hope
Virgil can convince

32:07.534 --> 32:09.101
these guys to help us out.

32:09.144 --> 32:11.103
I need you guys
to trust me.

32:11.146 --> 32:12.931
He will.

32:15.063 --> 32:16.456
Hey, Levi?

32:16.499 --> 32:17.848
- Yeah?
- Can I talk to you

32:17.892 --> 32:19.415
about something?

32:21.330 --> 32:25.465
I've been thinking
a lot lately about us.

32:25.508 --> 32:27.423
You know, and how things ended.

32:28.947 --> 32:32.689
The day you left for Germany--
- Eve, we've been over this.

32:32.733 --> 32:35.344
Leaving you has been the
biggest regret of my life.

32:35.388 --> 32:37.607
What the hell's
going on here?

32:37.651 --> 32:39.435
Get back to work!
[grunts]

32:39.479 --> 32:40.915
[grunting]
- Virgil!

32:40.959 --> 32:42.699
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:42.743 --> 32:44.353
[groaning]

32:44.397 --> 32:46.007
[grunting]
[blows landing]

32:46.051 --> 32:47.966
Levi, he's gonna kill him.

32:48.009 --> 32:49.097
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:49.141 --> 32:50.403
Ah!

32:51.404 --> 32:55.016
[struggling efforts]

32:55.060 --> 32:56.713
Get off me!

32:58.063 --> 33:00.282
You're gonna pay for that.

33:00.326 --> 33:02.371
Take him.

33:02.415 --> 33:04.025
No, wait! Wait! No!

33:04.069 --> 33:06.332
Where are you taking him?
Where are you taking him?

33:07.202 --> 33:08.987
Levi!

33:09.030 --> 33:10.684
We're almost there.

33:16.559 --> 33:18.213
Hey, you're thirsty.

33:18.257 --> 33:19.649
Here, drink.

33:19.693 --> 33:21.260
[sighs]

33:25.090 --> 33:28.571
[sighs] I thought you said
we were going in the back.

33:28.615 --> 33:30.486
This is the only way.

33:30.530 --> 33:32.227
No, no, no.

33:32.271 --> 33:34.229
There are guards everywhere.

33:34.273 --> 33:36.405
We'll be caught.

33:36.449 --> 33:38.451
That's the plan.

33:40.105 --> 33:43.325
<i>[ominous music]</i>

33:43.369 --> 33:46.067
[groans] Ohh--

33:46.111 --> 33:48.461
Wait, something's wrong.

33:48.504 --> 33:51.507
<i>♪</i>

33:51.551 --> 33:53.596
You--you drugged me.

33:53.640 --> 33:55.642
I'm sorry, my boy.

33:55.685 --> 33:57.818
This is where
I have to leave you.

33:57.861 --> 34:00.255
[groans]

34:00.299 --> 34:03.215
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:03.258 --> 34:07.523
<i>♪</i>

34:10.744 --> 34:12.746
This is Santa Monica Bay.

34:12.789 --> 34:16.141
Catalina Island is 26 miles
to the south,

34:16.184 --> 34:18.926
Channel Islands due west.

34:18.969 --> 34:20.971
According to my
spectrometer readings,

34:21.015 --> 34:24.453
it's their midpoint where
the next sinkhole will open.

34:24.497 --> 34:27.108
That event will create one
of the largest tidal waves

34:27.152 --> 34:29.676
this world has ever seen.

34:29.719 --> 34:31.112
How big?

34:31.156 --> 34:35.508
Enough to take out Malibu,
Santa Monica, Venice.

34:35.551 --> 34:38.467
- My dad lives here.
- It's going to happen.

34:38.511 --> 34:40.034
I'm sure of it.

34:40.078 --> 34:42.906
I just need to get people to
listen before it's too late.

34:42.950 --> 34:44.778
There's someone
I need to convince.

34:44.821 --> 34:49.826
I need you to tell me
what you know, please.

34:49.870 --> 34:52.307
You have no idea what it's
like to believe something

34:52.351 --> 34:53.830
that no one thinks is true.

34:55.963 --> 34:57.747
Actually, I do.

35:00.185 --> 35:04.841
For years, everyone thought my
dad was crazy, but he--

35:04.885 --> 35:07.148
but he wasn't.

35:07.192 --> 35:11.500
If someone had
just believed him,

35:11.544 --> 35:14.068
everything could
have been different.

35:14.112 --> 35:16.592
What are you saying?

35:16.636 --> 35:19.073
I know if we stay here,
the Hollywood sinkhole

35:19.117 --> 35:20.205
could close,
and we may never

35:20.248 --> 35:22.207
get back to our families.

35:22.250 --> 35:23.947
But we have to do this.

35:23.991 --> 35:26.907
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

35:26.950 --> 35:29.214
<i>♪</i>

35:29.257 --> 35:31.346
We'll tell you
everything we know.

35:31.390 --> 35:34.306
We're in.

35:34.349 --> 35:36.177
Great job clearing
the field today.

35:36.221 --> 35:39.485
By tomorrow, we'll be halfway
ready to start planting.

35:39.528 --> 35:41.487
Maybe closer if Judah ever
learns how to use a rake.

35:41.530 --> 35:43.053
Not my skill set.

35:47.971 --> 35:51.105
I'm sure your dad
and Silas made camp.

35:51.149 --> 35:53.412
Levi and your mom are
keeping each other safe.

35:53.455 --> 35:54.935
Yeah, I hope so.

35:54.978 --> 35:56.197
- Hey.
- Hey.

35:56.241 --> 35:57.720
Any luck finding Scott?

35:57.764 --> 35:59.983
None.

36:00.027 --> 36:02.116
I mean, I can't get rid of the
guy since I get down here,

36:02.160 --> 36:03.944
and then he's just gone?

36:05.467 --> 36:07.513
Something's not right.

36:13.214 --> 36:17.305
Veronica, you have a moment?

36:17.349 --> 36:19.612
Sure.

36:19.655 --> 36:22.049
But I don't want to talk about Lilly,

36:22.092 --> 36:24.225
or whatever her name is.

36:24.269 --> 36:27.228
Believe me, I understand.

36:27.272 --> 36:31.711
This is strange,
to say the least.

36:32.973 --> 36:35.671
I don't know why she
came back here, Ty.

36:37.543 --> 36:39.501
She cares about you.

36:41.677 --> 36:44.506
There are things
I've done that...

36:47.074 --> 36:48.597
can never be forgiven.

36:49.946 --> 36:51.209
What do you mean?

36:51.252 --> 36:54.212
<i>[somber music]</i>

36:54.255 --> 36:55.996
<i>♪</i>

36:56.039 --> 36:58.390
Good night, Ty.

36:59.913 --> 37:01.741
[sighs]

37:05.614 --> 37:07.529
[branches cracking]

37:07.573 --> 37:09.357
Who's there?

37:13.056 --> 37:14.580
Scott.

37:17.191 --> 37:18.671
You OK?

37:18.714 --> 37:21.282
You are never going to
believe what happened.

37:21.326 --> 37:25.199
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:25.243 --> 37:28.507
I've been thinking a lot
lately about how things ended

37:28.550 --> 37:30.204
about the day you left
for Germany.

37:30.248 --> 37:32.554
<i>[phone line trilling]</i>

37:37.385 --> 37:39.213
Come on, Levi.
Pick up.

37:39.257 --> 37:40.954
<i>You've reached
Captain Levi Delgado.</i>

37:40.997 --> 37:42.782
<i>Leave a message.
[beep]</i>

37:44.174 --> 37:47.134
[indistinct chatter]

37:47.177 --> 37:50.224
Levi! Levi!
[plane engine roaring]

37:50.268 --> 37:53.227
<i>[somber music]</i>

37:53.271 --> 37:56.665
<i>♪</i>

37:56.709 --> 38:00.321
- Be safe.
- We'll be good.

38:00.365 --> 38:02.062
Daddy.

38:02.105 --> 38:04.282
<i>♪</i>

38:04.325 --> 38:06.066
Be safe.

38:06.109 --> 38:13.029
<i>♪</i>

38:30.917 --> 38:32.875
[door opens]

38:32.919 --> 38:35.356
- Get in there!
- [grunts]

38:35.400 --> 38:37.532
[coughs, groans]

38:39.273 --> 38:41.493
[door slams]
- Levi.

38:41.536 --> 38:42.711
Hi.
- [groans]

38:42.755 --> 38:44.278
- Are you OK?
- I'm OK.

38:44.322 --> 38:46.062
Oh, God.

38:46.106 --> 38:51.416
<i>♪</i>

38:51.459 --> 38:54.375
I thought I lost you.

38:54.419 --> 38:56.943
I thought you had, too.
[both laugh]

38:56.986 --> 38:59.119
I told you,
I'm not going anywhere.

39:00.729 --> 39:03.297
I sat here for hours,
thinking you were gone.

39:03.341 --> 39:05.430
I know you feel guilty
about leaving me before,

39:05.473 --> 39:10.043
but the truth is, I let you go.

39:10.086 --> 39:11.610
The day you were supposed
to go to Germany,

39:11.653 --> 39:13.394
I went to the base.
I was gonna stop you.

39:13.438 --> 39:15.527
I--and I didn't.

39:16.832 --> 39:18.443
Because after Izzy's accident,
I just thought--

39:18.486 --> 39:20.967
I thought--

39:21.010 --> 39:22.272
I just thought
it was the right thing to do.

39:22.316 --> 39:26.015
And--and that was a mistake.

39:27.016 --> 39:32.065
I don't wanna keep anything
from you ever again because--

39:32.108 --> 39:34.197
Levi--

39:34.241 --> 39:35.721
Yeah?

39:35.764 --> 39:38.680
<i>[tender music]</i>

39:38.724 --> 39:45.861
<i>♪</i>

40:04.053 --> 40:05.881
[grunting]

40:09.537 --> 40:12.279
[gate chains rattling]

40:13.280 --> 40:16.239
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:16.283 --> 40:23.246
<i>♪</i>

40:40.220 --> 40:42.614
This will get
you out of the caves.

40:42.657 --> 40:45.094
It's a map.

40:45.138 --> 40:52.058
<i>♪</i>

40:57.193 --> 41:00.283
[men shouting]

41:00.327 --> 41:01.894
Silas--

41:03.504 --> 41:05.550
Get your family back.

41:05.593 --> 41:07.508
[chains rattling]

41:07.552 --> 41:14.646
<i>♪</i>

41:24.307 --> 41:26.440
All of you,

41:26.484 --> 41:27.876
move inside!

41:27.920 --> 41:29.748
[people clamoring]

41:29.791 --> 41:31.358
- You, come on!
- [grunts]

41:31.401 --> 41:33.534
All right, that's enough.
Get moving.

41:33.578 --> 41:35.362
Come on, you two up.

41:35.405 --> 41:37.146
[pushes]
- Ah--

41:37.190 --> 41:40.149
<i>[tense music]</i>

41:40.193 --> 41:41.368
<i>♪</i>

41:41.411 --> 41:43.370
Get up!
Keep moving!

41:43.413 --> 41:50.333
<i>♪</i>
